{"uid":"40784ddfeeb3f242","name":"DS_12P CNCL RFC callback with Version header returns 400","fullName":"functional-tests.tests.callbacks.test_RTP_callback_with_version_header#test_rfc_callback_DS_12P_CNCL_with_version_header","historyId":"9e9b08416189f5685aef1025c802977e","time":{"start":1784531299214,"stop":1784531301312,"duration":2098},"description":"\nDS_12P CNCL RFC callback sent with the Version header must be rejected with 400.\nThe RTP must remain in RFC_SENT (transition to CANCELLED must not happen).\n\nFlow:\n1. Activate payer, send RTP, trigger cancel via GPD DELETE → RFC_SENT\n2. Build a valid DS_12P CNCL payload\n3. POST to RFC callback endpoint WITH Version header\n4. Verify 400 is returned with the expected error body\n5. Verify RTP status is still RFC_SENT\n","descriptionHtml":"<p>DS_12P CNCL RFC callback sent with the Version header must be rejected with 400.<br />\nThe RTP must remain in RFC_SENT (transition to CANCELLED must not happen).</p>\n<p>Flow:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Activate payer, send RTP, trigger cancel via GPD DELETE → RFC_SENT</li>\n<li>Build a valid DS_12P CNCL payload</li>\n<li>POST to RFC callback endpoint WITH Version header</li>\n<li>Verify 400 is returned with the expected error body</li>\n<li>Verify RTP status is still RFC_SENT</li>\n</ol>\n","status":"passed","flaky":false,"newFailed":false,"newBroken":false,"newPassed":false,"retriesCount":0,"retriesStatusChange":false,"beforeStages":[{"name":"_session_faker","time":{"start":1784531044054,"stop":1784531044127,"duration":73},"status":"passed","steps":[],"attachments":[],"parameters":[],"stepsCount":0,"shouldDisplayMessage":false,"attachmentsCount":0,"hasContent":false,"attachmentStep":false},{"name":"rtp_consumer_access_token","time":{"start":1784531297949,"stop":1784531298337,"duration":388},"status":"passed","steps":[],"attachments":[],"parameters":[],"stepsCount":0,"shouldDisplayMessage":false,"attachmentsCount":0,"hasContent":false,"attachmentStep":false},{"name":"rtp_reader_acces